Deployment Failed

✖ Stack nodejs-project-prod failed to deploy (23s) 
✖ ServerlessError2: An error occurred: ApiLambdaFunction - Resource handler returned message: "Lambda function nodejs-project-prod-api could not be found"

❌ Error Meaning
	Lambda function nodejs-project-prod-api could not be found

👉 CloudFormation is trying to update an existing Lambda, but that Lambda doesn't exist anymore.
	This usually happens when:
	- You manually deleted the Lambda from AWS Console
	- Deployment was partially rolled back
	- Stack is in inconsistent state
	- Function name changed in serverless.yml

🔥 Option 1: Clean & Redeploy (Recommended)
	serverless remove		
	serverless deploy
	
	👉 This will:
		- Delete broken stack
		- Create fresh resources

⚡ Option 2: Force Deploy
	serverless deploy --force

🧹 Option 3: Delete Stack Manually
	AWS Console → CloudFormation
	Find stack: nodejs-project-prod & Delete it
	Deploy it again

