❗ What happens when you run serverless remove

   When you run:
	serverless remove

👉 Serverless deletes the entire CloudFormation stack:
	- Lambda functions
	- API Gateway
	- IAM roles
	- Everything tied to that service

🧠 Why this happens
	API Gateway URLs are based on:

	https://{api-id}.execute-api.{region}.amazonaws.com

✅ How to avoid endpoint change (Production Solution)
    🔥 Option 1: Use Custom Domain (Recommended)

	Set a fixed domain like:
	https://api.yourdomain.com

	Even if backend changes → URL stays same ✅
	
	Example in serverless.yml:
	   custom:
  		domainName: api.yourdomain.com

	   provider:
  		name: aws
  		runtime: nodejs20.x

	   plugins:
  		- serverless-domain-manager

   ⚡ Option 2: Don’t delete stack
	Instead of remove, fix using:
	serverless deploy --force

   🧹 Option 3: Export endpoint dynamically

       After deploy:
	
       serverless info
 		Use output in frontend / env:
		API_URL=https://new-id.execute-api.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com
